 [x] 📋 VTODO scheduling - Extend iTIP support to task delegation (same RFC 5546 patterns apply to VTODOs)

 [X] 🔄 Delegate declines - Handle the case where a delegate (Carol) declines the delegated invitation (should notify both organizer and original delegator)

 [x] 📝 Commit changes - Package up the RFC 5546 delegation work into a commit

 [X] 📅 RFC 7953 Calendar Availability - Implement VAVAILABILITY component for more sophisticated free/busy queries

 [X] 🔁 Recurring event delegation - Test/enhance delegation for specific occurrences of recurring events

 [X] Calendar Sharing/Delegation
  - Share calendars with read/write permissions
  - Delegate scheduling authority ("Alice can accept meetings for Bob")
  - Common in enterprise setups

 [X] 📖 Documentation - Update Radicale docs to describe the new scheduling features

 [X]  RFC 7986 - New iCalendar Properties
  COLOR:#FF5733          # Calendar item colors
  CONFERENCE:https://...  # Video call links (Zoom, Meet, Teams)
  IMAGE:https://...       # Event images/logos
  Modern calendar clients use these. Low effort, high value.

 [X] Managed Attachments (RFC 8607) Instead of inline base64 attachments, store them server-side with URLs. Better for large files and bandwidth.

---

## Potential Future Enhancements

 [X] 📧 Inbound email parsing - Parse incoming emails from external attendees (via webhook or IMAP)
  - Webhooks: SendGrid, Mailgun, Postmark, generic formats
  - IMAP polling: Background thread with configurable interval
  - CLI: `--imap-poll` for cron-based polling

 [X] 🔐 Attachment access control - Allow shared calendar users to access attachments
  - Integrated with SharingManager.check_share_access()
  - Both READ and READ_WRITE access can download attachments

 [X] 📊 Scheduling reports - CALDAV:calendar-query for schedule-inbox/outbox
  - Enable calendar-query, calendar-multiget on schedule-inbox/outbox
  - Time-range and component filtering supported
  - 9 comprehensive test cases in test_scheduling_reports.py

 [X] 🌐 CalDAV auto-scheduling - Server-side auto-accept for resources (SCHEDULE-AGENT=SERVER)
  - Implemented AutoScheduler class with configurable policies
  - Support for: always, if-free, manual, tentative-if-conflict
  - Per-resource policy configuration via JSON file
  - VAVAILABILITY integration for availability constraints
  - Comprehensive test suite in test_auto_scheduling.py
